Charles Lewis Napier [1] (12 April 1936 – 5 October 2011; age 75) was an actor from Scottsville, Kentucky who played two distinctive Star Trek characters in episodes which were made more than a quarter of a century apart. These roles were Adam in the Star Trek: The Original Series episode "The Way to Eden" and Lieutenant General Rex Denning in the Star Trek: Deep Space Nine episode "Little Green Men".
